==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Levulin
<hw>Lev"u*lin</hw> <pr>(l⟦ecr⟧v"⟦usl⟧*l⟦icr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A substance resembling dextrin, obtained from
the bulbs of the dahlia, the artichoke, and other sources, as a
colorless, spongy, amorphous material. It is so called because by
decomposition it yields <xex>levulose</xex>.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>l⟦ae⟧vulin</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Levulinic</ent>⟦br⟧
